/2/2025/02/avowed-seafarers-boots-treasure-map-location-solution-4.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=1920 1920w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/avowed-seafarers-boots-treasure-map-location-solution-4.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2048 2048w, https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/avowed-seafarers-boots-treasure-map-location-solution-4.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400 2400w\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/avowed-seafarers-boots-treasure-map-location-solution-4.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0%2C0%2C100%2C100\u0026amp;w=2400\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ccite\u003eImage: Obsidian Entertainment/Xbox Game Studios via Polygon\u003c/cite\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003eThis map shows you a river of red and a stone arch, with a broken stone tower looming in the distance. That tower is Tago’s Tower, east of the Deadfall Highlands, so the map location has to be even with the tower. The only possible area that fits the bill — river, red water, tower to the east — is a spot\u003cstrong\u003e north of the Sulfur Miner’s Basecamp\u003c/strong\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2025/02/avowed-seafarers-boots-treasure-map-location-solution-5.jpg?quality=90\u0026amp;strip=all\u0026amp;crop=0,0,100,100\" data-pswp-height=\"1440\" data-pswp-width=\"2560\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\"\u003e\u003cimg alt=\"The main character in Avowed looking at an arch in the Sulfur Miner’s camp area\" data-chromatic=\"ignore\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" data-nimg=\"fill\" sizes=\"(max-width: 639px) 100vw, (max-width: 1023px) 50vw, 700px\" srcset=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-co